args: Wait, you want to go into town?
Yes. You've been here training non-stop,\nand it's time for a break.
I appreciate the invitation, but right now,\nI have to master the Turbo Omega Shot.
A body needs rest, Patia. Even yours.
Indeed, muscles won't grow if you don't\nrest properly after putting them to use.
So perhaps a little change of pace\nis a good idea after all.
You came to this island for a vacation,\ndidn't you? So what do you say?
Well, I suppose I COULD use\na bit of a break...
SO MUCH FUN! Wooo! Now THIS is what\nvacation is supposed to look like!
Let's head to that general store next!\nOoo, and that food cart next to it\nlooks quite interesting as well!
If you can't decide, just do both.\nWe will examine the store first,\nthen pass by the cart.
For my part, I'm VERY curious about that\nice cream shop over there. Do you mind?
We set out to recharge ourselves today,\nso ice cream ahoy!
Heh. I'm glad you seem to be enjoying\nyourself so much, Patia.
It's because of you. Although I do wonder\nif it's okay to be having fun like this when\nBarbary is still out there.
If you're worried about that, you should\nadd in some training before bed.
After that, I'll treat you to my special\nspirogyra-and-liver smoothie!

It's an armsmaster specialty made by
combining highly nutritious slimes,
medicinal herbs, and raw liver.
Perfect for building muscle mass!
Is THAT why you were off buying\ningredients while we were enjoying\nour ice cream?!
I prefer not to vomit before bed, thank you.\nAlso, I have other things to do this night.
Do your plans have anything to do with\nthe little souvenir you bought earlier?
H-how did you know about that?!
My eyes are naturally drawn to the details.\nI hope he enjoys your surprise.
Th-there's no deep meaning to it!\nI just wanted to...convey my gratitude...
You're worrying quite a bit for something\nthat you claim has so little value.
I just... Look, it's hard to pick something\nthat perfectly expresses feelings, okay?!

If only I could convey all my feelings with
one swing of the Loving Hand like my
grandmother, I could've gotten through it
without worrying so much.
My grandmother had the ability to use\nthe Loving Hand to stir a person's very\nsoul. It's a skill I'm still trying to perfect.
Ah, I understand perfectly. I've had to work\nto get better at expressing myself as well.

I may have inherited great strength from
my ancestors, but when it comes to
Elisanne, I find myself overly passionate
without even realizing it.
I can see by the way your muscles tense\nthat you two are kindred spirits.
You could tell that much just by\nwatching their muscles?!
Yes, it's a specialty of mine.\nDid I not mention it?
No, you did not. It seems there is still\nmuch we do not know about each other.
That's because being so focused on\ndefeating Barbary has us doing nothing\nbut training all this time.
Huh. This day off may have been\nmore helpful than I imagined.
Our bonds are growing so much, I don't\nthink ANY opponent can defeat us!
Haw! Looks like we got us some ladies\nwho think they're hot stuff. Right, brah?
We're the toughest toughs around—\nthe Volleybrahs!
You lot are the outsiders foamin' at\nthe mouth to take down Barbary, yeah?
News flash, ladies—me and my brah are\ngonna be the ones to take out Barbary,\nso make like a beach and pound sand!
Hey! What's the big idea throwing that\nball around in the middle of town?!
Not runnin', eh? Looks like we'll have to\nsettle this the old-fashioned way...
Unless yer CHICKEN! Baaaawk bawk bawk!
Patia, I think we're being challenged\nto street volleyball!
I'd only heard of it in rumors!\nWhat will we do, Patia?
Bwaaa ha ha! Plucky bunch, ain't ya?!\nRight then, usual rules: First to three wins,\nor ya lose if ya get knocked unconscious.
First serve goes to us! Get ready to\nrun home cryin' to mama when I\nshow ya...the Net Melter!
He's got his own ultimate shot!\nBut it'll take more than that...\nCelliera, to the rear!
Brah. BRAH. They blocked your shot, brah!
It'll take more than that for you idiots\nto defeat OUR training!
Grrr... Fine then! Let's see how ya like\nmy Mad Pecs Slurveball!
There's no curve Julietta can't handle!
Braaaah! We're down by TWO, brah!\nNone'a the local teams even scored\na single point on us before!

You're much too weak, yet you chose to
challenge us to a street volleyball game—
and now you're going to be served!
...Ooo, but I AM clever.
Maybe you can pick up a few pointers\nfor the next time you want to try and\nchallenge a clearly superior opponent.
Am I imagining things, or is our\npassing crisper than before?
It's not your imagination. Our break today\nhas deepened our team's mutual\nunderstanding of one another.
And now that we know each other's\nspecial skills, maybe we can...
Everyone, I want to try something!\nOn the next serve, I need Verica and\nCelliera on support!
Estelle and Julietta, get in front with me!\nWe're going do a team attack!
The heck are they blabbin' about\nover there, brah?
In this formation—and these conditions—\nwe can do this. Estelle, focus power in\nyour right leg and hit the ball to Julietta!
Think of the Loving Hand, and put all of\nyour feelings into the strike!
I get it now... Here you go, Julietta!\nTake all of my desire for victory!
Julietta, tighten your muscles and release\nyour power! Give it everything you have!
I can feel your thoughts\nAND your strength...
Behold the power of our bonds!
*pant* *pant* We...we did it...\nWe learned the ultimate shot!
Now we can teach Barbary a lesson\nonce and for all!
Thank you—ALL of you. I never could\nhave done this without you.
Are you ready for one final push?
But we're counting on you to\nlead the way, Captain.
This time, we WILL taste victory!
